<paragraph blockId="36.[189,1398,1463,1525]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1900" box="[189,332,1463,1489]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megarhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,332,1463,1489]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Megarhyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mostly a Holarctic and Oriental genus, with one species introduced into 
<collectingCountry box="[1239,1347,1463,1489]" name="Australia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[189,346,1499,1525]" name="New Zealand" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
for biocontrol purposes, and a single species reported from the Afrotropical Region.
</paragraph>
